<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="view/macro:page/onecolumn"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
  <body>
    <h1 metal:fill-slot="heading">Projects in Launchpad</h1>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

<p style="font-size: normal; float: right; width: 15em; padding: 0.5em;
border: 1px solid green; margin: 0.5em; margin-left: 1em">
Hi there! This is a message from the team that develops Launchpad (this
is <a href="/~launchpad/+mugshots">what we look like</a> if you're
curious).  We're working hard to make sure Launchpad is the best project
hosting and registration site out there. We hope you enjoy it here.

<br />
<br />

PS: do <a href="/feedback">tell us</a> if you don't!
</p>

<h2>A brand new project in Launchpad</h2>

<p style="font-size: larger">
Launchpad is a service for <b>registering and hosting software
projects</b>. Service is provided free for open source/free software
projects. But let us steal a minute of your time to point out a few
important things before you proceed with the actual registration.
</p>

<ul style="font-size: larger">
  <li><b>Want to test drive Launchpad?</b>
  If you want a volatile test area, use <a
  href="https://staging.launchpad.net/"><b>staging.launchpad.net</b></a>,
  our code staging instance. You can use that server to create sample
  projects, file random bugs and even push throw-away branches, all
  without disturbing the community actively using Launchpad.

  <li style="margin-top: 1em"><b>Not sure what Launchpad is?</b> It's
  many things (and sometimes a bit confusing); check out <a
  href="https://help.launchpad.net/FeatureHighlights">our user
  handbook</a> or, if you prefer, <a
  href="https://launchpad.net/+tour">take our guided tour</a>.

  <li style="margin-top: 1em"><b>Is the project already registered?</b>
  Launchpad is both a hosting and a registration facility, and someone
  else may have already registered the project.
  <br />
  <b style="margin-left: 1em">Check here:</b>
  <form style="display: inline; font-size: smaller" action="/projects">
    <input type="text" name="text" />
    <input type="submit" value="go!" />
  </form>
  <br />
  <ul style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  <li>If you find a project you own, <a href="/launchpad/+addquestion">ask
  here</a> and we'll hand the project over to you.
  <li>If you want to translate that project to your language, <a
  href="/rosetta/+addquestion">ask here first</a>.
  </ul>

  <li style="margin-top: 1em"><b>Requesting Ubuntu CDs</b> is done at <a
  href="https://shipit.ubuntu.com/">shipit.ubuntu.com</a>
  <form style="display: inline; font-size: smaller"
        action="https://shipit.ubuntu.com/">
    <input type="submit" value="Oh, I want Ubuntu CDs" />
  </form>
  <br /><small>(this
  may sound weird to you, but a lot of people register projects asking
  for CDs!)</small>


  <li style="margin-top: 1em; list-style-type: circle">All set?
  Move on to <a href="/projects/+new"><b>the registration form</b></a>.
  Thanks for listening!
</ul>

</div>

</body>
</html>
